  "id": "bravery_shaken",
  "title": "When Courage Crumbles",
  "description": "Something shows you the real cost of courage, and now you're not sure it's worth it.",
  "content": "You were brave. You took the risk, made the sacrifice, stood up when it mattered. And it went badly. Maybe you got hurt. Maybe someone you tried to protect suffered anyway. Maybe your boldness made things worse instead of better. The failure doesn't just sting—it undermines the entire premise of courage. What if being brave is just being stupid? What if caution was the right answer all along? The fear you used to face now seems entirely reasonable.",
