    {
      "id": "recommit_to_courage",
      "text": "Courage means showing up even after failure",
      "description": "Being brave once is easy. Staying brave after getting hurt is what matters.",
      "resultText": "You acknowledge the failure and the pain, but you refuse to let them define what courage means. Yes, it went badly this time. That doesn't mean bravery itself is wrong. You process the hurt, tend your wounds, and then—when you're ready—you step up again. Not recklessly, but deliberately. This is what true courage looks like: not the absence of fear or the guarantee of success, but the willingness to try anyway.",
